<br />The video in that thread has part of the answer.  There are hardware recordings from a crapload of different Famicom board revisions, and IMHO it seems to prove definitively that there never was an "accurate" expansion sound, at least in cases where games use the NES internal channels at the same time (so it's especially notable on FDS stuff since it doesn't stand alone very much).  The balance differences are really huge.

		

